fr.ens.biologie.generic

Interface Textable


  • public interface Textable

    For relatively complex objects that can return information with various levels of detail. Taken from former Aot Node methods.

    Author:
    gignoux - 25 ao√ªt 2017

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default java.lang.String toDetailedString()
      Displays the object with all the detailed of its content, for screen or console display purpose.
      default java.lang.String toShortString()
      Displays the object as simply as possible, with no guarantee that another object will not return the same string.
      default java.lang.String toUniqueString()
      Displays the object as simply as possible, showing its unicity as an instance.

    • Method Detail

      • toUniqueString

        default java.lang.String toUniqueString()
        Displays the object as simply as possible, showing its unicity as an instance. Typically, it should show the object address + some indication of the object content. Or if the object has a unique ID (e.g. graph elements), it should use it.
        Returns:

      • toShortString

        default java.lang.String toShortString()
        Displays the object as simply as possible, with no guarantee that another object will not return the same string.
        The returned description must fit on one single, short (~20 character), line of text.
        Returns:

      • toDetailedString

        default java.lang.String toDetailedString()
        Displays the object with all the detailed of its content, for screen or console display purpose. (ex. for AOT Nodes: show all properties + list of edge ids)
        Returns:
